        By using our website, you agree to the Terms and Privacy Policy.
    </p>
</div>

<!-- Terms and Conditions -->
<div class="mt-5">
    <h3>Terms and Conditions</h3>

    <h4>1. Acceptance of Terms</h4>
    <p>
        By accessing or using Tubbataha Explorer, you agree to comply with these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree, please refrain from using the platform.
    </p>

    <h4>2. Purpose of the Platform</h4>
    <p>
        Tubbataha Explorer is an educational tool designed to analyze, showcase, and share information about marine species in the Tubbataha Reef and promote conservation efforts.
    </p>

    <h4>3. User Responsibilities</h4>
    <p>
        You agree to use the platform for educational purposes only. All submitted content must be original, accurate, and free of harmful or misleading information. You are prohibited from uploading content that is offensive, illegal, or violates the intellectual property rights of others.
    </p>

    <h4>4. Data Submission and File Uploads</h4>
    <p>
        By submitting files or other data, you grant Tubbataha Explorer a non-exclusive license to use, display, and share your content for educational purposes. All uploads are subject to review to ensure compliance with the platform’s goals and standards.
    </p>

    <h4>5. Data Collection</h4>
    <p>
        Tubbataha Explorer collects and stores user-uploaded data to enhance the collective knowledge about marine species and conservation practices. For more information, refer to our Privacy Notice below.
    </p>

    <h4>6. Disclaimer</h4>
    <p>
        The information shared on Tubbataha Explorer is for educational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional environmental or biological advice. The platform is not responsible for the accuracy of user-submitted data.
    </p>

    <h4>7. Modification of Terms</h4>
    <p>
        We reserve the right to amend these Terms and Conditions at any time. Users will be notified of changes via the platform.
    </p>

    <h4>8. Termination</h4>
    <p>
        Violation of these Terms may result in suspension or termination of access to Tubbataha Explorer.
    </p>
</div>

<!-- Privacy Notice -->
<div class="mt-5">
    <h3>Privacy Notice for Data Collection</h3>

    <h4>1. Data We Collect</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>User-provided information: Uploaded files, descriptions, titles, and other metadata.</li>
        <li>Personal data: Name, email address, and any data necessary for account management.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2. Purpose of Data Collection</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Facilitate sharing and analysis of marine species information.</li>
        <li>Promote educational initiatives and conservation practices.</li>
        <li>Improve the functionality and user experience of Tubbataha Explorer.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Data Security</h4>
    <p>
        We use appropriate measures to protect your data. However, no system can guarantee complete security, and you share data at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h4>4. Your Rights</h4>
    <p>
        You have the right to request access, correction, or deletion of your personal data. For inquiries, please contact us via the provided support email.
    </p>
</div>
